data.current_summary: Retrieve flight restrictions applicable along route.
data.current_description:
Retrieve Flight Restrictions applicable along your route. Request body parameters are:
* route:  [GeoJSON Linestring](https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc7946.html#appendix-A) defining the route. Max allowed length is 50 km.
data.description_suggestion: Retrieve Temporary Flight Restrictions (TFRs) applicable along a specified route. Accepts a GeoJSON LineString defining the flight route (max 50 km length). Returns all active and published TFRs that intersect the route. Check the startDateTime and endDateTime properties in the response to determine if restrictions apply during your planned operation time. Note: Even if a TFR is present, flight may be possible via waiver through the Special Governmental Interest (SGI) process.
data.reasoning: Description lacks clarity about what TFRs are returned (active/published), what the response contains (startDateTime/endDateTime properties), and important context about SGI waivers. data.current_summary: Retrieve all special security areas located within given distance of location.
data.current_description:
Retrieve special security areas existing within given distance from a point. Request body parameters are:
* latitude:  WGS84 latitude coordinate of your selected point, in decimal degrees
* longitude:  WGS84 longitude coordinate of your selected point, in decimal degrees
* distance:  distance in meters (max allowed value is 25000)
data.description_suggestion: Retrieve Special Security Areas (SSAs) within a specified distance from a geographic point. Accepts WGS84 latitude/longitude coordinates and a search radius in meters (max 25,000 m). Returns all SSAs where UAS flight operations are prohibited without prior FAA authorization and coordination with the controlling agency. These restrictions remain in effect 24/7 until further announcement. Response includes location, boundaries, and agency contact information for coordination.
